  "description": [
    "Immigration Board Set Up by Truman To Study Policies President Truman yesterday set up a sevenman Commission on Immigration and Naturalization headed by former Solicitor Gen eral Philip B Perlman to study and evaluate the Immigration and naturalization policies of the Unit ed States The President created the new agency as an aftermath of pas sage by Congress over his veto of the controversial McCarranWal ter Bill codifying the immigration and naturalization laws The President bitterly assailed the measure at the time it be came law declaring that it would discriminate against many races and prevent the United States from caring adequately for the displaced persons problem He urged in connection with his veto that Congress set up a commission to study the whole matter but nothing was done In his statement today announcing the new commission he expressed the hope that its study be com pleted before reconvening of the next Congress Sets Up 3 Main Goals He set up three major goals for the commission saying it should give particular attention to 1 The requirements and ad ministration of our immigration laws with respect to the admis sion naturalization and denatu ralization of aliens and their exclusion and"
  ],
